WEBVTT

00:00:01.230 --> 00:00:04.692 line:90% position:50% align:center
Welcome to JW Broadcasting®.

00:00:04.692 --> 00:00:09.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
This month marks ten years
since the first program debuted.

00:00:09.905 --> 00:00:12.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll take a look at the special role

00:00:12.157 --> 00:00:15.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
JW Broadcasting has played
in uniting God’s people.

00:00:16.704 --> 00:00:21.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
In Part 1 of the episode
of <i>Applying Bible Principles,</i>

00:00:21.417 --> 00:00:25.838 line:90% position:50% align:center
James and Linda were too focused
on when the end would come.

00:00:25.838 --> 00:00:30.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll see how they now help others
keep a balanced view of the future.

00:00:31.844 --> 00:00:33.929 line:90% position:50% align:center
In <i>Iron Sharpens Iron,</i>

00:00:33.929 --> 00:00:37.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’ll learn how to put our website
to better use in the ministry.

00:00:38.225 --> 00:00:41.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
This is the October 2024 edition

00:00:41.353 --> 00:00:43.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
of JW Broadcasting.

00:01:02.416 --> 00:01:04.835 line:10% position:50% align:center
When I first began serving at Bethel,

00:01:04.835 --> 00:01:07.087 line:10% position:50% align:center
I’d call home to speak with my family

00:01:07.087 --> 00:01:09.131 line:10% position:50% align:center
and my mother would always ask,

00:01:09.131 --> 00:01:10.633 line:10% position:50% align:center
“Have they told you when the date

00:01:10.633 --> 00:01:12.176 line:10% position:50% align:center
of Armageddon is?”

00:01:12.885 --> 00:01:15.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though she was being humorous
and didn’t expect an answer,

00:01:15.679 --> 00:01:18.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
her question reveals what we all long for

00:01:18.807 --> 00:01:22.353 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Jehovah’s promised new world.

00:01:22.353 --> 00:01:25.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe you have, in a sense,
asked Jehovah that question,

00:01:25.522 --> 00:01:28.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
“How much longer, Jehovah?”

00:01:28.192 --> 00:01:31.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or you’ve said to Jehovah:
“I’m exhausted.

00:01:31.445 --> 00:01:35.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I don’t know how much longer
I can keep going.

00:01:35.199 --> 00:01:39.662 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Please, Jehovah, when will your promises
for a world of lasting peace,

00:01:39.662 --> 00:01:43.916 line:90% position:50% align:center
refreshment, and relief from the pressures
of this world come true?”

00:01:45.042 --> 00:01:48.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
We all likely feel this way
from time to time.

00:01:48.253 --> 00:01:51.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
What can help us not give up,

00:01:51.215 --> 00:01:55.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
not give out, in our spiritual battle?

00:01:55.260 --> 00:01:59.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
Note the words of Jesus at Mark 13:29.

00:02:00.933 --> 00:02:05.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice what he says: “Likewise also you,

00:02:05.521 --> 00:02:08.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
“when you see these things happening,

00:02:08.190 --> 00:02:11.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
know that he is near at the doors.”

00:02:11.193 --> 00:02:14.446 line:90% position:50% align:center
What things would we see happening?

00:02:15.531 --> 00:02:18.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
Prophecy being fulfilled.

00:02:18.951 --> 00:02:23.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we recognize Bible prophecies
being fulfilled before our eyes,

00:02:23.247 --> 00:02:25.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
our faith is fortified.

00:02:25.374 --> 00:02:27.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
We see that the end is imminent.

00:02:27.668 --> 00:02:31.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
We recognize that we’re almost done.

00:02:31.755 --> 00:02:35.092 line:90% position:50% align:center
That helps us not give out.

00:02:35.092 --> 00:02:37.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
What are some of these prophecies?

00:02:37.469 --> 00:02:40.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re familiar with the prophecies
of earthquakes,

00:02:40.389 --> 00:02:43.225 line:90% position:50% align:center
“wars and reports of wars,”
food shortages,

00:02:43.225 --> 00:02:45.644 line:90% position:50% align:center
and disease all happening at once.

00:02:45.644 --> 00:02:48.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You see these things happening.”

00:02:48.939 --> 00:02:51.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
We see the diminished love of God

00:02:51.650 --> 00:02:55.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the deteriorating attitude
of people in general,

00:02:55.529 --> 00:02:58.490 line:90% position:50% align:center
as foretold in 2 Timothy chapter 3.

00:02:59.616 --> 00:03:02.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second Timothy 3:13 says:

00:03:02.161 --> 00:03:04.580 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Wicked men and impostors

00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:07.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
will advance from bad to worse.”

00:03:07.416 --> 00:03:11.086 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You see these things happening.”

00:03:11.086 --> 00:03:15.007 line:90% position:50% align:center
As foretold, “this good news
of the Kingdom” is being preached worldwide

00:03:15.007 --> 00:03:17.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
—now in over 1,000 languages.

00:03:17.301 --> 00:03:19.928 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You see these things happening.”

00:03:19.928 --> 00:03:22.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
As a result of Christ’s rule,

00:03:22.181 --> 00:03:25.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
the knowledge of Jehovah
is abundantly overflowing.

00:03:25.309 --> 00:03:28.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You see these things happening.”

00:03:28.520 --> 00:03:31.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what about Isaiah 45:18?

00:03:31.940 --> 00:03:35.527 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here Jehovah calls himself
the “Maker” of the earth,

00:03:35.527 --> 00:03:38.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
“who did not create it simply for nothing,

00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:41.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
but formed it to be inhabited.”

00:03:41.950 --> 00:03:46.955 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, scientists say that the world
is on the brink of becoming uninhabitable.

00:03:46.955 --> 00:03:51.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
They warn that if action to stop
global warming is not taken quickly,

00:03:51.668 --> 00:03:54.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
its compounding effects
will become irreversible.

00:03:56.048 --> 00:03:58.300 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Revelation 11:18,

00:03:58.300 --> 00:04:01.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Bible foretold that in our day,

00:04:01.136 --> 00:04:04.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
man would be “ruining the earth,”

00:04:04.181 --> 00:04:06.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it also assures us

00:04:06.433 --> 00:04:11.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will step in
and not let the earth be completely ruined.

00:04:12.606 --> 00:04:16.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some may wonder how much worse
things will get.

00:04:16.068 --> 00:04:19.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
Interestingly, at Luke 17:20,

00:04:19.404 --> 00:04:21.406 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus said this

00:04:21.406 --> 00:04:23.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Luke 17:20:

00:04:23.450 --> 00:04:27.996 line:90% position:50% align:center
“The Kingdom of God
is not coming with striking observableness.”

00:04:29.248 --> 00:04:33.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
This means that world conditions
during the last days

00:04:33.127 --> 00:04:35.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
would not be so extreme

00:04:35.212 --> 00:04:38.882 line:90% position:50% align:center
that people would be forced to believe
that the end is near.

00:04:38.882 --> 00:04:42.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
As Matthew 24:37-39 indicates,

00:04:42.845 --> 00:04:45.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
they would still be “eating and drinking,”

00:04:45.264 --> 00:04:48.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
getting married,
and able to carry on their everyday lives.

00:04:49.476 --> 00:04:52.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
How should this affect us?

00:04:52.229 --> 00:04:56.483 line:90% position:50% align:center
It should fortify us not to give up.

00:04:56.483 --> 00:04:58.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Mark 13:35,

00:04:58.735 --> 00:05:02.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus said we must “keep on the watch.”

00:05:02.030 --> 00:05:05.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
This means to stay awake and be on guard.

00:05:05.659 --> 00:05:08.704 line:90% position:50% align:center
And in the parallel account in Matthew 24,

00:05:08.704 --> 00:05:12.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jesus connects this with being ready.

00:05:14.126 --> 00:05:18.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
What will help us to do this
when we feel so exhausted?

00:05:18.672 --> 00:05:21.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
Where can we get strength
to keep up the fight?

00:05:23.051 --> 00:05:26.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
In a word—trust.

00:05:27.347 --> 00:05:30.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
We all love Jehovah.

00:05:31.602 --> 00:05:33.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
We want to be convinced

00:05:33.645 --> 00:05:37.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Jehovah’s loyal love for us individually.

00:05:38.859 --> 00:05:43.655 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can we trust that he’ll always
be there to help us?

00:05:44.698 --> 00:05:48.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice on-screen the assurance Jehovah gives

00:05:48.076 --> 00:05:51.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Hebrews 13:5:

00:05:53.207 --> 00:05:55.959 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I will never leave you,

00:05:55.959 --> 00:05:59.004 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I will never abandon you.”

00:06:00.005 --> 00:06:04.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has been sustaining us.

00:06:04.635 --> 00:06:06.720 line:90% position:50% align:center
Think how he sustains you.

00:06:07.596 --> 00:06:12.559 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe you’ve experienced
the ravages of a natural disaster;

00:06:12.559 --> 00:06:15.646 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has sustained you.

00:06:15.646 --> 00:06:18.649 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe you’ve dealt
with the loss of a loved one;

00:06:18.649 --> 00:06:21.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has sustained you.

00:06:21.526 --> 00:06:23.695 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whatever trial we’ve gone through,

00:06:23.695 --> 00:06:27.824 line:90% position:50% align:center
we can see how Jehovah has helped us.

00:06:27.824 --> 00:06:32.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
This confirms for us
that he’ll sustain us in the future.

00:06:32.287 --> 00:06:34.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we have the confidence

00:06:34.581 --> 00:06:37.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s stated at Psalm 46:1, 2:

00:06:38.919 --> 00:06:42.547 line:90% position:50% align:center
“God is our refuge and strength,

00:06:42.547 --> 00:06:46.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
“a help that is readily found
in times of distress.

00:06:46.885 --> 00:06:50.722 line:90% position:50% align:center
“That is why we will not fear,
though the earth undergoes change,

00:06:50.722 --> 00:06:53.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
though the mountains topple
into the depths of the sea.”

00:06:54.810 --> 00:06:59.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
These emphatic expressions leave no doubt

00:06:59.106 --> 00:07:02.192 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah will care for us.

00:07:03.610 --> 00:07:06.405 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why is this reminder so important?

00:07:07.614 --> 00:07:10.659 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, verse 6 of Hebrews chapter 13

00:07:10.659 --> 00:07:14.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
links trust with courage.

00:07:14.121 --> 00:07:16.581 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice what it says:

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:22.546 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So that we may be of good courage and say:

00:07:22.546 --> 00:07:27.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘‘‘Jehovah is my helper;
I will not be afraid.

00:07:27.217 --> 00:07:29.219 line:90% position:50% align:center
What can man do to me?’”

00:07:30.137 --> 00:07:33.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice it doesn’t say <i>our </i> or <i>their </i> helper.

00:07:33.724 --> 00:07:36.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
It says “my helper.”

00:07:36.268 --> 00:07:38.270 line:90% position:50% align:center
We love Jehovah.

00:07:38.270 --> 00:07:41.440 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can also be absolutely convinced

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:45.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Jehovah loves us
and will help us individually.

00:07:47.529 --> 00:07:51.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times, it can be difficult
to trust that Jehovah loves us personally

00:07:51.867 --> 00:07:54.411 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will act in our behalf.

00:07:54.411 --> 00:07:58.915 line:90% position:50% align:center
What can help build our trust
in Jehovah’s love?

00:07:58.915 --> 00:08:01.460 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s discuss three ways.

00:08:01.460 --> 00:08:03.962 line:90% position:50% align:center
First, Proverbs 15

00:08:03.962 --> 00:08:06.590 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Proverbs 15, notice verse 9:

00:08:06.590 --> 00:08:11.136 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Jehovah detests the way of the wicked one,

00:08:11.136 --> 00:08:16.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
but he loves the one
who pursues righteousness.”

00:08:17.309 --> 00:08:19.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He loves the one

00:08:19.936 --> 00:08:24.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
who pursues
[or, chases after] righteousness.”

00:08:25.192 --> 00:08:28.612 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knows we can’t be perfectly righteous.

00:08:28.612 --> 00:08:32.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
But he loves us for trying our best,

00:08:32.157 --> 00:08:35.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he said, ‘for pursuing righteousness.’

00:08:35.619 --> 00:08:38.622 line:90% position:50% align:center
He loves us because we don’t quit.

00:08:38.622 --> 00:08:42.125 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can trust that he’ll never abandon us

00:08:42.125 --> 00:08:46.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we don’t give up
in pursuing righteousness.

00:08:47.547 --> 00:08:52.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
Second, pour out your heart to Jehovah.

00:08:52.469 --> 00:08:55.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
Lamentations 2:19 says this

00:08:55.764 --> 00:08:58.683 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Lamentations 2:19:

00:08:58.683 --> 00:09:01.937 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Pour out your heart like water

00:09:01.937 --> 00:09:03.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
before the face of Jehovah.”

00:09:04.898 --> 00:09:09.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
It doesn’t say,
“Pour out your mind” or “your thoughts”

00:09:09.611 --> 00:09:12.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
but “pour out your heart”

00:09:12.280 --> 00:09:17.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that includes our feelings,
our concerns, our anxieties.

00:09:17.285 --> 00:09:21.039 line:90% position:50% align:center
We pour out our heart
like one pours out water

00:09:21.039 --> 00:09:23.083 line:90% position:50% align:center
—not holding anything back.

00:09:24.209 --> 00:09:26.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we express to our heavenly Father

00:09:26.837 --> 00:09:29.798 line:90% position:50% align:center
our love and appreciation for him,

00:09:29.798 --> 00:09:32.801 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we tell him our concerns and desires,

00:09:32.801 --> 00:09:35.345 line:90% position:50% align:center
and when we ask for his direction,

00:09:35.345 --> 00:09:38.849 line:90% position:50% align:center
we show that we value
our friendship with him.

00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:42.436 line:90% position:50% align:center
What will be the result for you?

00:09:42.436 --> 00:09:45.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
The more you pour out your heart like water

00:09:45.188 --> 00:09:48.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
and feel his personal response to you,

00:09:48.316 --> 00:09:51.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
the more you’ll sense his love for you

00:09:51.361 --> 00:09:55.282 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the more you’ll trust
that he’ll never abandon you.

00:09:55.282 --> 00:09:59.578 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your gratitude for Jehovah’s
enduring love will increase.

00:10:00.996 --> 00:10:04.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, third, remember that trials

00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:08.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
do not mean a loss of Jehovah’s favor.

00:10:08.044 --> 00:10:11.465 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our enemy knows that feeling close to Jehovah

00:10:11.465 --> 00:10:14.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
is the source of our strength.

00:10:14.301 --> 00:10:17.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
So he’ll try to undermine our confidence,

00:10:17.429 --> 00:10:20.599 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he hopes that we break away from Jehovah.

00:10:20.599 --> 00:10:25.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, when Job
was undergoing a severe trial,

00:10:25.437 --> 00:10:30.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
his false comforters lyingly said
that the reason for these trials

00:10:30.442 --> 00:10:32.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
was that he’d lost Jehovah’s favor.

00:10:34.196 --> 00:10:37.908 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah reminded Job to look at creation

00:10:37.908 --> 00:10:41.703 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to see His love and wisdom.

00:10:42.829 --> 00:10:45.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did faithful Job respond?

00:10:45.582 --> 00:10:48.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
He said at Job 42:5:

00:10:49.544 --> 00:10:52.714 line:90% position:50% align:center
“My ears have heard about you,

00:10:52.714 --> 00:10:57.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
but now I do see you with my eyes.”

00:10:58.094 --> 00:11:01.389 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may wonder if we’ve lost Jehovah’s favor.

00:11:01.389 --> 00:11:04.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
We should ask Jehovah to help us see him

00:11:04.768 --> 00:11:09.231 line:90% position:50% align:center
and see his loyal love for us every day.

00:11:09.231 --> 00:11:11.858 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ask him to help you use this trial

00:11:11.858 --> 00:11:15.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
as a stepping stone to love
and trust him even more.

00:11:17.447 --> 00:11:22.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve discussed one way
we get ready for the upcoming events

00:11:22.285 --> 00:11:27.290 line:90% position:50% align:center
—build our trust that Jehovah
has loyal love for us individually.

00:11:28.375 --> 00:11:31.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
Trusting that Jehovah will never abandon us

00:11:31.127 --> 00:11:33.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
gives us the strength to keep up the fight

00:11:33.755 --> 00:11:36.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
and keep on the watch.

00:11:36.508 --> 00:11:38.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
At Ephesians 6:16,

00:11:38.510 --> 00:11:42.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
faith, or trust, in Jehovah
is compared to a shield

00:11:42.973 --> 00:11:47.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
—a shield “with which you [can] extinguish
all the wicked one’s burning arrows,”

00:11:47.394 --> 00:11:50.647 line:90% position:50% align:center
or all of Satan’s spiritual attacks.

00:11:50.647 --> 00:11:55.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, when we hear lies about Jehovah,

00:11:55.026 --> 00:11:59.114 line:90% position:50% align:center
his organization,
and those he’s appointed to take the lead,

00:11:59.114 --> 00:12:01.157 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will not be shaken.

00:12:01.157 --> 00:12:04.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
We won’t give up or give out.

00:12:04.869 --> 00:12:09.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
We know the prophecy
at Matthew 24:45 has been fulfilled.

00:12:09.416 --> 00:12:12.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has lovingly provided a slave

00:12:12.419 --> 00:12:15.297 line:90% position:50% align:center
who’s “faithful and discreet.”

00:12:16.423 --> 00:12:21.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
We recognize that Jehovah
provides spiritual food and direction

00:12:21.052 --> 00:12:24.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
through this body of men at the right time.

00:12:24.472 --> 00:12:27.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re not left floundering
or trying to find our way.

00:12:27.726 --> 00:12:30.645 line:90% position:50% align:center
Therefore, we remain obedient

00:12:30.645 --> 00:12:34.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
and responsive to the direction we receive.

00:12:34.441 --> 00:12:36.443 line:90% position:50% align:center
We never dismiss it,

00:12:36.443 --> 00:12:40.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
even if it doesn’t appear practical
from a human standpoint.

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:44.618 line:90% position:50% align:center
Trusting in Jehovah’s loyal love

00:12:44.618 --> 00:12:46.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
has saved his people in the past.

00:12:48.204 --> 00:12:53.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
At 2 Chronicles 20:1, 2,

00:12:53.126 --> 00:12:57.088 line:90% position:50% align:center
it tells us that Jehoshaphat
learned that a coalition of nations

00:12:57.088 --> 00:12:59.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
—“a large crowd . . . from the region
of the sea”—

00:12:59.549 --> 00:13:01.885 line:90% position:50% align:center
were coming against him.

00:13:01.885 --> 00:13:06.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat already had the habit
of turning to Jehovah.

00:13:06.181 --> 00:13:10.268 line:90% position:50% align:center
“He resolved to search for Jehovah.”

00:13:10.268 --> 00:13:13.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did he and his faithful subjects do this?

00:13:13.563 --> 00:13:18.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat poured his heart out
like water to Jehovah.

00:13:18.985 --> 00:13:20.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice in verse 12

00:13:20.987 --> 00:13:25.241 line:90% position:50% align:center
how he expresses
his complete trust in Jehovah:

00:13:27.369 --> 00:13:32.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
“For we are powerless before this large crowd
that is coming against us;

00:13:32.207 --> 00:13:35.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and we do not know what we should do,

00:13:35.210 --> 00:13:38.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
but our eyes are toward you.”

00:13:39.506 --> 00:13:42.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did Jehovah respond?

00:13:42.008 --> 00:13:44.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice verse 15.

00:13:44.302 --> 00:13:48.848 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah sent Jahaziel to reassure them:

00:13:48.848 --> 00:13:52.936 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do not be afraid or be terrified
because of this large crowd,

00:13:52.936 --> 00:13:56.815 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the battle is not yours but God’s.”

00:13:57.691 --> 00:14:00.151 line:90% position:50% align:center
The strategy that Jehoshaphat followed

00:14:00.151 --> 00:14:02.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
didn’t seem practical
from a human standpoint.

00:14:03.613 --> 00:14:05.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehoshaphat appointed singers

00:14:05.615 --> 00:14:09.244 line:90% position:50% align:center
dressed “in holy adornment”
to praise Jehovah.

00:14:09.244 --> 00:14:13.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
And how unusual that he put them
in front of the armed men!

00:14:14.708 --> 00:14:17.043 line:90% position:50% align:center
Were they singing songs about how Jehovah

00:14:17.043 --> 00:14:20.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
defeated their enemies in past wars?

00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:21.631 line:90% position:50% align:center
No.

00:14:21.631 --> 00:14:26.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
They sang about Jehovah’s loyal love.

00:14:27.470 --> 00:14:28.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
What was the result?

00:14:28.888 --> 00:14:32.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah confused their enemies,
and they attacked each other.

00:14:34.227 --> 00:14:37.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
What lessons can we learn from this account?

00:14:37.856 --> 00:14:42.694 line:90% position:50% align:center
Trusting Jehovah includes
trusting his representatives.

00:14:42.694 --> 00:14:46.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
The lifesaving direction we receive
from Jehovah’s organization

00:14:46.656 --> 00:14:50.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
may not appear practical
from a human standpoint.

00:14:50.452 --> 00:14:53.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
But we recognize
the fulfillment  of the prophecy

00:14:53.496 --> 00:14:55.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Matthew 24:45

00:14:55.498 --> 00:14:57.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
about “the faithful and discreet slave,”

00:14:57.667 --> 00:15:00.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’re ready to obey
any instruction they provide.

00:15:02.046 --> 00:15:06.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, getting ready includes building trust

00:15:06.718 --> 00:15:11.598 line:90% position:50% align:center
and being convinced that Jehovah
will deliver us from the wicked one.

00:15:13.141 --> 00:15:15.977 line:90% position:50% align:center
Trusting Him will help us understand

00:15:15.977 --> 00:15:18.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
the prophetic role
of “the faithful and discreet slave”

00:15:18.897 --> 00:15:22.233 line:90% position:50% align:center
during this time of the end
when Jehovah is using them

00:15:22.233 --> 00:15:26.070 line:90% position:50% align:center
to provide lifesaving direction.

00:15:26.070 --> 00:15:30.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
This direction is helping us to stay ready.

00:15:31.576 --> 00:15:34.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has sustained us in the past,

00:15:34.412 --> 00:15:37.791 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he sustains us now.

00:15:39.667 --> 00:15:41.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
Seeing these things happening

00:15:41.961 --> 00:15:46.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
can also fortify and strengthen us.

00:15:47.258 --> 00:15:50.470 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many of you have been fighting
to “keep on the watch”

00:15:50.470 --> 00:15:52.847 line:90% position:50% align:center
for many years.

00:15:52.847 --> 00:15:56.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now the end is clearly in sight.

00:15:56.309 --> 00:15:58.812 line:90% position:50% align:center
We don’t want to give up now.

00:15:58.812 --> 00:16:03.817 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice the reassurance at Galatians 6:9

00:16:04.818 --> 00:16:08.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Galatians 6:9:

00:16:08.530 --> 00:16:12.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
“So let us not give up in doing what is fine,

00:16:12.784 --> 00:16:15.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
“for in due time we will reap

00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:18.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
if we do not tire out.”

00:16:19.415 --> 00:16:21.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because of our imperfect flesh

00:16:21.709 --> 00:16:24.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the efforts of Satan
and this wicked world,

00:16:24.671 --> 00:16:29.175 line:90% position:50% align:center
we must constantly battle
negative influences.

00:16:29.175 --> 00:16:33.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some of you dear brothers and sisters
must fight hard every day

00:16:33.638 --> 00:16:36.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
to maintain your relationship with Jehovah.

00:16:36.349 --> 00:16:37.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t give up!

00:16:39.561 --> 00:16:42.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
Your fight has not been in vain.

00:16:42.146 --> 00:16:44.399 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’ve made the right choices.

00:16:44.399 --> 00:16:46.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has seen your loyal love for him,

00:16:46.818 --> 00:16:50.321 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he treasures your devotion.

00:16:50.321 --> 00:16:53.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
Time and time again,
you’ve made sacrifices

00:16:53.658 --> 00:16:56.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
and left your comfort zone
to give Jehovah your best,

00:16:56.452 --> 00:17:00.206 line:90% position:50% align:center
to stay active in the ministry,
to keep taking in spiritual food,

00:17:00.206 --> 00:17:03.334 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to teach your children
how to speak about Jehovah.

00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:08.131 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah loves you dearly for this

00:17:08.131 --> 00:17:13.094 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will loyally continue
to help you until the battle is won.

00:17:13.094 --> 00:17:15.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do not give up now!

00:17:16.931 --> 00:17:20.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
And you young ones,
Jehovah loves you too.

00:17:20.435 --> 00:17:24.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knows that you’re growing up
in a world that’s broken.

00:17:24.397 --> 00:17:28.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knows that it can be hard for you
to maintain hope for the future.

00:17:28.484 --> 00:17:32.071 line:90% position:50% align:center
Please, never forget that your God,

00:17:32.071 --> 00:17:36.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
your heavenly Father, loves you dearly.

00:17:36.159 --> 00:17:40.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never forget that your future is bright.

00:17:41.456 --> 00:17:44.709 line:90% position:50% align:center
Whether we’re young or old or in between,

00:17:44.709 --> 00:17:46.961 line:90% position:50% align:center
we will not give up.

00:17:46.961 --> 00:17:48.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’re so close.

00:17:48.796 --> 00:17:52.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
We see these things happening
with our own eyes.

00:17:52.967 --> 00:17:57.347 line:90% position:50% align:center
So we’ll keep on the watch,
we’ll trust Jehovah with all our hearts,

00:17:57.347 --> 00:17:59.557 line:90% position:50% align:center
we’ll trust Jehovah’s arrangements,

00:17:59.557 --> 00:18:03.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we will not give out
in our spiritual battle,

00:18:03.186 --> 00:18:07.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we will reap
rich blessings soon—very soon.

00:18:11.110 --> 00:18:13.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can you believe it’s been ten years

00:18:13.738 --> 00:18:16.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
since JW Broadcasting began?

00:18:16.699 --> 00:18:20.036 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s 120 monthly programs!

00:18:20.036 --> 00:18:22.664 line:90% position:50% align:center
These programs have unified

00:18:22.664 --> 00:18:25.917 line:90% position:50% align:center
and strengthened Jehovah’s organization.

00:18:25.917 --> 00:18:30.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the next video, we’ll be reminded
of some gems we’ve received

00:18:30.755 --> 00:18:34.342 line:90% position:50% align:center
and we’ll hear personal stories
that illustrate the impact

00:18:34.342 --> 00:18:37.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
JW Broadcasting has had on the brotherhood.

00:18:48.272 --> 00:18:50.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
We warmly welcome you,

00:18:50.775 --> 00:18:52.360 line:90% position:50% align:center
dear brothers and sisters,

00:18:52.360 --> 00:18:53.569 line:90% position:50% align:center
for our first

00:18:53.569 --> 00:18:57.073 line:90% position:50% align:center
JW Broadcasting® monthly program.

00:19:01.369 --> 00:19:03.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Christian neutrality.”

00:19:03.246 --> 00:19:04.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
Modesty.

00:19:04.998 --> 00:19:06.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do the Math.”

00:19:06.666 --> 00:19:10.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Deal With Anxiety
One Day at a Time.”

00:19:10.837 --> 00:19:15.591 line:90% position:50% align:center
“[Children] are an inheritance
from Jehovah.”

00:19:15.591 --> 00:19:19.178 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah loves each one of us

00:19:19.178 --> 00:19:23.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
despite our appearances
or imperfections.

00:19:24.600 --> 00:19:28.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
A marriage that has good patterns
shaped by Jehovah’s principles

00:19:28.396 --> 00:19:32.108 line:90% position:50% align:center
looks like this well-balanced family circle.

00:19:32.108 --> 00:19:34.485 line:90% position:50% align:center
Though we’re tainted with sin,

00:19:34.485 --> 00:19:38.197 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah does not discard
imperfect humans.

00:19:38.197 --> 00:19:42.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
We may worry about
what might seem to be big tests,

00:19:42.702 --> 00:19:45.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
only to find
that they’re not as overwhelming

00:19:45.496 --> 00:19:47.498 line:90% position:50% align:center
as we feared they would be.

00:19:48.624 --> 00:19:52.879 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each individual grain of sand
reveals distinct beauty. . . .

00:19:52.879 --> 00:19:56.132 line:90% position:50% align:center
That is how Jehovah sees each of you.

00:19:56.132 --> 00:19:57.633 line:10% position:50% align:center
My personal favorite thing

00:19:57.633 --> 00:19:59.218 line:10% position:50% align:center
about JW Broadcasting

00:19:59.218 --> 00:20:00.595 line:10% position:50% align:center
has to be that there are videos

00:20:00.595 --> 00:20:02.096 line:10% position:50% align:center
on really anything,

00:20:02.096 --> 00:20:04.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
whether it’s something
to help me in school

00:20:04.432 --> 00:20:06.601 line:90% position:50% align:center
or something to help me
in my spiritual life.

00:20:06.601 --> 00:20:08.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
We like to theme our family worship.

00:20:08.478 --> 00:20:11.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
Recently,
we did a family worship on neutrality.

00:20:11.481 --> 00:20:16.319 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we found a lot of great videos
that specifically had to do with that.

00:20:16.319 --> 00:20:18.112 line:90% position:50% align:center
I use my device quite a bit,

00:20:18.112 --> 00:20:20.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I don’t like it to get in the way

00:20:20.573 --> 00:20:23.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
of schoolwork and family time.

00:20:23.367 --> 00:20:26.329 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the video has really helped me

00:20:26.329 --> 00:20:29.665 line:90% position:50% align:center
manage my screen time so it doesn’t
get in the way of those things.

00:20:29.665 --> 00:20:33.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
Being able to see brothers and sisters

00:20:33.127 --> 00:20:36.464 line:90% position:50% align:center
from all over the world,
all different ages, all different backgrounds

00:20:36.464 --> 00:20:38.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
serving Jehovah

00:20:38.049 --> 00:20:40.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
—it’s helped me personally.

00:20:40.301 --> 00:20:43.679 line:90% position:50% align:center
But I think it’s really helped the kids
in setting their own spiritual goals

00:20:43.679 --> 00:20:47.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
and being able to see

00:20:47.100 --> 00:20:51.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
that there’s so much that can be done
in Jehovah’s organization,

00:20:51.020 --> 00:20:54.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
no matter what their interests are,
and that Jehovah can take care of them.

00:20:54.857 --> 00:20:57.860 line:90% position:50% align:center
We feel part
of Jehovah’s worldwide organization.

00:20:57.860 --> 00:21:00.988 line:90% position:50% align:center
And, you know, at the end of the broadcast,
they say, “We love you, friends.”

00:21:00.988 --> 00:21:02.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s really no substitute for that.

00:21:03.574 --> 00:21:06.661 line:10% position:50% align:center
As a special pioneer,

00:21:06.661 --> 00:21:09.288 line:10% position:50% align:center
the pandemic lasted so long.

00:21:10.790 --> 00:21:12.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I had various sources of stress.

00:21:13.626 --> 00:21:16.212 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, fortunately,
it was the direction

00:21:16.212 --> 00:21:19.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
from the discreet slave,
a motherlike organization,

00:21:19.757 --> 00:21:22.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
that gave us direction
every step of the way.

00:21:23.636 --> 00:21:25.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was great.

00:21:26.139 --> 00:21:29.100 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Governing Body taught us principles

00:21:29.100 --> 00:21:31.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
and gave us so much support.

00:21:33.396 --> 00:21:36.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s been such a joy
to hear in the Governing Body updates

00:21:36.566 --> 00:21:39.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
that many inactive ones are coming back.

00:21:43.239 --> 00:21:47.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
I visited a single brother
who was inactive for 24 years.

00:21:50.538 --> 00:21:54.000 line:90% position:50% align:center
And he said several times
how he wanted to come back.

00:21:56.544 --> 00:21:58.754 line:90% position:50% align:center
I was really happy that I acted

00:21:58.754 --> 00:22:00.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
on the message
from the Governing Body updates.

00:22:03.384 --> 00:22:05.887 line:90% position:50% align:center
It really strengthened my faith.

00:22:09.849 --> 00:22:13.352 line:90% position:50% align:center
In one Governing Body update from 2022,

00:22:13.352 --> 00:22:16.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
they highlighted our return
to the in-person ministry.

00:22:20.109 --> 00:22:22.111 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt like a brand-new publisher

00:22:22.111 --> 00:22:24.739 line:90% position:50% align:center
when we went out
in the field ministry again.

00:22:26.824 --> 00:22:30.620 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt like a baby, a toddler, in a way.

00:22:32.580 --> 00:22:34.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
So my wife and I
prayed a lot to Jehovah

00:22:34.582 --> 00:22:37.126 line:90% position:50% align:center
for us to be able
to have good conversations

00:22:37.126 --> 00:22:39.795 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to be able
to muster up the courage needed.

00:22:41.589 --> 00:22:44.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
When we actually went
from house to house,

00:22:44.217 --> 00:22:46.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
to our surprise,
householders were willing to listen.

00:22:50.598 --> 00:22:53.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
We felt the support of the holy spirit

00:22:53.476 --> 00:22:56.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
and felt the kindness and help
from the Governing Body

00:22:56.395 --> 00:22:58.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the pandemic.

00:23:00.191 --> 00:23:02.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
So this gives us the motivation to overcome 

00:23:02.735 --> 00:23:06.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
any obstacle in our way,
no matter what the future holds.

00:23:09.742 --> 00:23:12.161 line:90% position:50% align:center
I’m really appreciative of that.

00:23:14.121 --> 00:23:16.374 line:10% position:50% align:center
I got baptized when I was 25 years old.

00:23:18.417 --> 00:23:21.671 line:10% position:50% align:center
What contributed to me becoming inactive

00:23:21.671 --> 00:23:24.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
was the lack of Bible study,

00:23:24.090 --> 00:23:27.260 line:90% position:50% align:center
neglecting my meeting attendance,

00:23:27.260 --> 00:23:29.303 line:90% position:50% align:center
and some bad associations.

00:23:30.888 --> 00:23:33.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
I remained inactive for ten years.

00:23:35.518 --> 00:23:39.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
The JW Broadcasting program
that helped me to return to Jehovah

00:23:41.065 --> 00:23:43.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
was the program from February 2016,

00:23:46.112 --> 00:23:48.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
where we find the experience
of Brother Derrick,

00:23:50.032 --> 00:23:52.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
who similarly had strayed away
from Jehovah.

00:23:54.328 --> 00:23:56.998 line:90% position:50% align:center
But he recognized
that he had made a big mistake,

00:23:56.998 --> 00:23:59.166 line:90% position:50% align:center
which caused him many problems.

00:24:00.668 --> 00:24:02.837 line:90% position:50% align:center
So I could relate to Brother Derrick.

00:24:03.963 --> 00:24:06.090 line:90% position:50% align:center
And so, I said,

00:24:06.090 --> 00:24:08.884 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Why can’t I return to Jehovah?”

00:24:10.511 --> 00:24:12.596 line:90% position:50% align:center
That video helped me fix matters

00:24:12.596 --> 00:24:15.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
and get close to Jehovah little by little.

00:24:17.768 --> 00:24:19.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ve been able to watch
Gilead School talks

00:24:19.895 --> 00:24:22.106 line:90% position:50% align:center
and some broadcasts as a family.

00:24:22.898 --> 00:24:25.109 line:90% position:50% align:center
It has helped us to expand our friendships

00:24:25.109 --> 00:24:27.236 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our brothers in the congregation.

00:24:29.196 --> 00:24:32.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
I remember a Gilead School talk
that was given by Brother David Splane

00:24:32.450 --> 00:24:36.203 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the theme
“If You Look for It, You Will Find It.”

00:24:38.247 --> 00:24:40.416 line:90% position:50% align:center
That taught us that when we want
to expand our friendships

00:24:40.416 --> 00:24:43.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our brothers in the congregation,

00:24:43.502 --> 00:24:46.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
we should not focus on their defects,

00:24:46.422 --> 00:24:49.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we should look more
at their good qualities.

00:24:49.717 --> 00:24:51.802 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that helped us as a family

00:24:51.802 --> 00:24:54.805 line:90% position:50% align:center
to remain united
with all those in the congregation.

00:24:56.849 --> 00:25:00.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
I really like everything
that comes out on JW Broadcasting.

00:25:02.063 --> 00:25:04.690 line:90% position:50% align:center
But what I love the most

00:25:04.690 --> 00:25:06.942 line:90% position:50% align:center
are the experiences
of our brothers and sisters

00:25:06.942 --> 00:25:11.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
who remain steadfast
and keep their faith in Jehovah.

00:25:12.698 --> 00:25:14.700 line:90% position:50% align:center
I love family worship so much

00:25:14.700 --> 00:25:16.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
because we get to sit down as a family

00:25:16.994 --> 00:25:19.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
and practice some Kingdom songs,

00:25:19.705 --> 00:25:23.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
read a Bible story,
or watch the broadcast for the month.

00:25:24.543 --> 00:25:27.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
The first time I went to a convention
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:25:27.755 --> 00:25:30.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
it was like ten thousand people.

00:25:30.257 --> 00:25:32.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I went in there and I saw

00:25:32.301 --> 00:25:35.179 line:90% position:50% align:center
all these different faces
and different colors,

00:25:35.179 --> 00:25:38.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
it was like Jehovah showing me:
“Hey, Rafika,

00:25:38.140 --> 00:25:41.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
“remember you were asking me
about all different people getting together

00:25:41.811 --> 00:25:43.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and being one?

00:25:43.687 --> 00:25:47.358 line:90% position:50% align:center
See, I’m not partial;
they do get along; we are unified.”

00:25:48.192 --> 00:25:51.237 line:90% position:50% align:center
To know that you have
a heavenly Father

00:25:51.237 --> 00:25:53.948 line:90% position:50% align:center
who cares about you

00:25:53.948 --> 00:25:56.742 line:90% position:50% align:center
—that was the best feeling on earth.

00:25:56.742 --> 00:25:58.953 line:90% position:50% align:center
I never thought that God had a name.

00:26:00.454 --> 00:26:04.583 line:90% position:50% align:center
And ever since that day on,
I never forget Jehovah’s name.

00:26:04.583 --> 00:26:06.585 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s superglued in my heart.

00:26:07.586 --> 00:26:09.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our love for Jehovah

00:26:09.964 --> 00:26:13.008 line:90% position:50% align:center
and our determination
to live by his standards

00:26:13.008 --> 00:26:15.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
are being tested each day.

00:26:15.511 --> 00:26:18.514 line:90% position:50% align:center
And yet,
because we’re being well-fed spiritually,

00:26:18.514 --> 00:26:22.852 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have everything we need
to meet those tests with joy.

00:26:24.979 --> 00:26:26.939 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dear brothers and sisters,

00:26:26.939 --> 00:26:28.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
please be assured

00:26:28.941 --> 00:26:30.734 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the warm love

00:26:30.734 --> 00:26:33.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Governing Body
and our prayers in your behalf.

00:26:35.448 --> 00:26:37.825 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

00:26:37.825 --> 00:26:40.744 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting®.

00:26:44.665 --> 00:26:47.501 line:90% position:50% align:center
What program was special to you?

00:26:47.501 --> 00:26:49.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you remember one?

00:26:49.503 --> 00:26:52.673 line:90% position:50% align:center
We encourage you
to rewatch the spiritual food

00:26:52.673 --> 00:26:55.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
that’s been presented in past programs.

00:26:55.217 --> 00:26:59.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we thank Jehovah
for making all this possible.

00:27:00.848 --> 00:27:04.435 line:90% position:50% align:center
Have you ever watched the news
and thought: ‘Is this it?

00:27:04.435 --> 00:27:07.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
Is this the beginning
of the great tribulation?’

00:27:07.688 --> 00:27:11.442 line:90% position:50% align:center
In a previous episode
of <i>Apply Bible Principles,</i>

00:27:11.442 --> 00:27:16.280 line:90% position:50% align:center
James and Linda learned
to change their focus and maintain joy.

00:27:16.280 --> 00:27:18.699 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now they’ll help a young brother do the same.

00:32:30.427 --> 00:32:33.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
We can’t control when the end will come,

00:32:33.472 --> 00:32:36.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
but we can control who we are when it does.

00:32:36.725 --> 00:32:41.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
Maybe like Thulani, you wonder
if the sacrifices you made were worth it.

00:32:42.523 --> 00:32:44.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
Francis Páez del Rosario

00:32:44.983 --> 00:32:48.278 line:90% position:50% align:center
made sacrifices as an accomplished musician

00:32:48.278 --> 00:32:50.489 line:90% position:50% align:center
to focus on the Kingdom.

00:32:50.489 --> 00:32:54.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
Her life story was featured
in the August 2005 <i>Awake!</i>

00:32:54.493 --> 00:32:57.871 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see how she views her choices
in the next segment.

00:33:05.963 --> 00:33:08.549 line:90% position:50% align:center
My dad sold the house
to buy musical instruments

00:33:08.549 --> 00:33:12.010 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that us children
could become great artists.

00:33:14.513 --> 00:33:16.557 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we achieved just that.

00:33:23.522 --> 00:33:25.482 line:90% position:50% align:center
We made it to the top.

00:33:29.403 --> 00:33:31.613 line:90% position:50% align:center
My dancing style became so famous

00:33:31.613 --> 00:33:34.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
that they would advertise
with only a picture of me.

00:33:34.950 --> 00:33:36.702 line:90% position:50% align:center
Wherever they put that image,

00:33:36.702 --> 00:33:39.371 line:90% position:50% align:center
everyone knew Los Rosario would be there.

00:33:51.508 --> 00:33:53.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
I really liked dancing.
I loved it.

00:33:53.552 --> 00:33:58.473 line:90% position:50% align:center
I loved the makeup, the clothes, the stage.

00:33:58.473 --> 00:33:59.850 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was me.

00:34:00.809 --> 00:34:03.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
But after the concerts were over,

00:34:03.687 --> 00:34:05.814 line:90% position:50% align:center
I felt empty.

00:34:07.566 --> 00:34:11.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s nothing like the happiness
that comes from knowing

00:34:11.069 --> 00:34:13.614 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’re doing what’s right before Jehovah.

00:34:15.032 --> 00:34:17.034 line:90% position:50% align:center
That happiness doesn’t fade,

00:34:17.034 --> 00:34:20.579 line:90% position:50% align:center
and it will always be there
because it comes from Jehovah.

00:34:29.963 --> 00:34:31.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
When I decided to leave the group,

00:34:31.965 --> 00:34:34.009 line:90% position:50% align:center
my dad was not pleased.

00:34:35.719 --> 00:34:37.971 line:90% position:50% align:center
He had worked so hard for it.

00:34:40.724 --> 00:34:45.687 line:90% position:50% align:center
Things got, um,

00:34:45.687 --> 00:34:47.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
difficult.

00:34:49.399 --> 00:34:51.735 line:90% position:50% align:center
This opposition really pained me

00:34:51.735 --> 00:34:56.448 line:90% position:50% align:center
because my dad and I
had always enjoyed a beautiful friendship.

00:34:56.448 --> 00:34:58.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
We were very close.

00:35:00.118 --> 00:35:04.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
Despite the way he treated us,
we never disrespected him.

00:35:04.539 --> 00:35:06.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
We were always kind to him.

00:35:06.667 --> 00:35:09.044 line:90% position:50% align:center
And because of that,

00:35:09.044 --> 00:35:12.047 line:90% position:50% align:center
little by little he started to soften.

00:35:13.840 --> 00:35:17.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
One day, one of my sons asked,

00:35:17.135 --> 00:35:19.262 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Why don’t you invite him to a meeting?”

00:35:19.262 --> 00:35:21.807 line:90% position:50% align:center
My dad’s eyes lit up, and he said,

00:35:21.807 --> 00:35:24.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
“I’ve been wanting to go for some time now.”

00:35:24.184 --> 00:35:26.520 line:90% position:50% align:center
And we started studying with him.

00:35:27.729 --> 00:35:30.023 line:90% position:50% align:center
He knew that he had found the truth.

00:35:32.567 --> 00:35:35.946 line:90% position:50% align:center
He enrolled in the school;
he gave his first part.

00:35:37.114 --> 00:35:41.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
So the truth really touched him deeply.

00:35:41.994 --> 00:35:45.831 line:90% position:50% align:center
I asked him one day during the study:

00:35:45.831 --> 00:35:49.376 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Dad, tell me, what do you think now?

00:35:49.376 --> 00:35:53.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Do you think I made a good decision
in leaving the group

00:35:53.422 --> 00:35:55.924 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and following this path

00:35:55.924 --> 00:35:59.344 line:90% position:50% align:center
and dedicating my life to Jehovah?”

00:35:59.344 --> 00:36:02.014 line:90% position:50% align:center
He looked at me and said:

00:36:02.014 --> 00:36:04.266 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You did well.

00:36:04.266 --> 00:36:07.144 line:90% position:50% align:center
“You made a very good decision.

00:36:07.144 --> 00:36:12.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
I only wish I had been able
to raise all of you in the truth.”

00:36:14.568 --> 00:36:17.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dad saw his children succeed,
accomplish so much,

00:36:17.738 --> 00:36:20.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
and see their dreams come true.

00:36:21.575 --> 00:36:25.370 line:90% position:50% align:center
But he realized that that wasn’t everything.

00:36:27.622 --> 00:36:30.208 line:90% position:50% align:center
He realized that true happiness

00:36:30.208 --> 00:36:33.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
comes from serving the Creator, Jehovah God.

00:36:34.212 --> 00:36:36.506 line:90% position:50% align:center
It reminded me
of the words of the apostle Paul

00:36:36.506 --> 00:36:38.967 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Philippians 3:8.

00:36:38.967 --> 00:36:41.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
He said that he considered what he did before

00:36:41.553 --> 00:36:43.597 line:90% position:50% align:center
“as a lot of refuse.”

00:36:44.931 --> 00:36:46.600 line:90% position:50% align:center
We felt the same.

00:36:46.600 --> 00:36:49.394 line:90% position:50% align:center
We were willing to leave everything behind.

00:36:50.353 --> 00:36:54.566 line:90% position:50% align:center
After a concert,
there was that emptiness inside.

00:36:54.566 --> 00:36:56.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s so different to the way I feel

00:36:56.818 --> 00:37:00.238 line:90% position:50% align:center
after a meeting with the brothers and sisters

00:37:00.989 --> 00:37:03.867 line:90% position:50% align:center
or after I give a Bible study

00:37:05.869 --> 00:37:08.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
or after a day serving at Bethel
with Roberto, my husband.

00:37:09.247 --> 00:37:12.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
That happiness doesn’t go away.

00:37:12.209 --> 00:37:14.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s nothing better than that.

00:37:23.428 --> 00:37:26.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
Francis doesn’t focus on what could’ve been

00:37:26.181 --> 00:37:29.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
but on the blessings of the present.

00:37:29.309 --> 00:37:32.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
She’s seen the seeds of truth
take root within her family

00:37:32.395 --> 00:37:34.481 line:90% position:50% align:center
and now happily serves as a commuter

00:37:34.481 --> 00:37:37.526 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the Dominican Republic branch
with her husband.

00:37:38.777 --> 00:37:43.240 line:90% position:50% align:center
She isn’t the only one
who followed this successful formula.

00:37:43.240 --> 00:37:45.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see who else from the Bible

00:37:45.450 --> 00:37:48.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
followed the same pattern
in this morning worship.

00:37:49.788 --> 00:37:52.999 line:10% position:50% align:center
Our Scripture text and article highlight

00:37:52.999 --> 00:37:55.293 line:10% position:50% align:center
the importance of submission

00:37:55.293 --> 00:37:58.672 line:10% position:50% align:center
and why we should submit to Jehovah.

00:37:58.672 --> 00:38:00.882 line:10% position:50% align:center
Of course, we find it a pleasure

00:38:00.882 --> 00:38:03.301 line:10% position:50% align:center
to submit to Jehovah because we love him.

00:38:03.301 --> 00:38:06.221 line:10% position:50% align:center
That’s why we submit to Jehovah.

00:38:06.221 --> 00:38:10.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
But there is that occasion
when submitting to Jehovah is difficult.

00:38:10.475 --> 00:38:11.560 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s hard.

00:38:11.560 --> 00:38:15.480 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perhaps we have to take a firm stand
in front of opposers.

00:38:15.480 --> 00:38:16.940 line:90% position:50% align:center
We have to stand up for Jehovah.

00:38:16.940 --> 00:38:19.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
That means we stick out from the world.

00:38:19.818 --> 00:38:21.611 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s hard.

00:38:21.611 --> 00:38:24.573 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or perhaps we have to change something
in our personal life

00:38:24.573 --> 00:38:29.119 line:90% position:50% align:center
to bring our life more in harmony
with Jehovah’s will and standards.

00:38:29.119 --> 00:38:30.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s hard.

00:38:31.329 --> 00:38:33.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
Or perhaps we want
to give wholehearted support

00:38:33.623 --> 00:38:35.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
to an organizational adjustment
or arrangement

00:38:35.834 --> 00:38:37.878 line:90% position:50% align:center
that we don’t fully understand.

00:38:37.878 --> 00:38:39.880 line:90% position:50% align:center
That may be hard.

00:38:39.880 --> 00:38:42.883 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what can help us?

00:38:42.883 --> 00:38:47.846 line:90% position:50% align:center
Confidence that God is with his people.

00:38:49.264 --> 00:38:54.269 line:90% position:50% align:center
If we know that God is with his people,
with us,

00:38:54.269 --> 00:38:56.521 line:90% position:50% align:center
then we know he will bless us.

00:38:56.521 --> 00:39:00.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
Each time we’re going to make
any adjustment in our life

00:39:00.567 --> 00:39:05.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
or submit to Jehovah’s way of doing things,
we’re going to get a blessing.

00:39:05.030 --> 00:39:07.532 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can we have such confidence?

00:39:07.532 --> 00:39:09.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
Absolutely.

00:39:09.117 --> 00:39:13.705 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, we can say
that Jehovah gives us signs,

00:39:13.705 --> 00:39:17.792 line:90% position:50% align:center
or solid evidence, that he is with us.

00:39:17.792 --> 00:39:19.794 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example, let’s open our Bibles

00:39:19.794 --> 00:39:23.340 line:90% position:50% align:center
to Isaiah chapter 7.

00:39:23.340 --> 00:39:25.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s go back in time

00:39:25.508 --> 00:39:29.804 line:90% position:50% align:center
and review this historical account
in Isaiah chapter 7.

00:39:30.972 --> 00:39:34.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
The background is in verses 1 and 2,

00:39:34.351 --> 00:39:37.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
during the days of King Ahaz.

00:39:37.103 --> 00:39:39.522 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s see what we can learn.

00:39:39.522 --> 00:39:44.361 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Now in the days of Ahaz son of Jotham
son of Uzziah, the king of Judah,

00:39:44.361 --> 00:39:46.863 line:90% position:50% align:center
“King Rezin of Syria

00:39:46.863 --> 00:39:51.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and Pekah son of Remaliah,
the king of Israel,

00:39:51.076 --> 00:39:54.287 line:90% position:50% align:center
“came up to wage war against Jerusalem,

00:39:54.287 --> 00:39:56.289 line:90% position:50% align:center
“but he could not capture it.

00:39:57.415 --> 00:39:59.668 line:90% position:50% align:center
“A report was made to the house of David:

00:39:59.668 --> 00:40:03.964 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Syria has joined forces with Ephraim.’

00:40:03.964 --> 00:40:07.926 line:90% position:50% align:center
“And the heart of Ahaz
and the heart of his people

00:40:07.926 --> 00:40:12.138 line:90% position:50% align:center
began to tremble, like the trees
of the forest shaking in the wind.”

00:40:13.431 --> 00:40:16.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, it’s true;
the situation was terrifying.

00:40:16.476 --> 00:40:19.771 line:90% position:50% align:center
Both the king of Israel and the king of Syria
joined forces.

00:40:19.771 --> 00:40:22.565 line:90% position:50% align:center
They declared war on Judah.

00:40:22.565 --> 00:40:23.650 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:40:23.650 --> 00:40:26.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
They wanted to dethrone Ahaz as the king

00:40:26.987 --> 00:40:31.533 line:90% position:50% align:center
and replace him with another man, perhaps
one who was not in the line of David.

00:40:32.742 --> 00:40:37.163 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, what a triumph that would be for Satan
if he could install

00:40:37.163 --> 00:40:41.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
his own diabolical dynasty
on the throne in Jerusalem!

00:40:41.251 --> 00:40:43.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would Jehovah allow that?

00:40:44.212 --> 00:40:46.840 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did Ahaz do?
What effect did it have on him?

00:40:46.840 --> 00:40:49.759 line:90% position:50% align:center
Did he show faith and confidence in Jehovah?

00:40:50.969 --> 00:40:53.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
He began to tremble in fear.

00:40:53.263 --> 00:40:55.557 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 2 says tremble in fear,

00:40:55.557 --> 00:40:59.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
“like the trees of the forest shaking
in the wind”—no faith at all.

00:41:00.603 --> 00:41:02.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what does Jehovah do?

00:41:02.772 --> 00:41:05.525 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, verse 11,

00:41:05.525 --> 00:41:08.403 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah continued speaking to Ahaz:

00:41:08.403 --> 00:41:11.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Ask for a sign from Jehovah . . . ;

00:41:11.656 --> 00:41:14.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
[make it] as deep as the Grave
or as high as the sky.”

00:41:14.367 --> 00:41:16.578 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Ahaz, just ask for a sign.

00:41:16.578 --> 00:41:18.121 line:90% position:50% align:center
I want to help you.’

00:41:19.664 --> 00:41:21.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what does Ahaz say?

00:41:21.082 --> 00:41:23.710 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘No, I’m not going to ask for a sign.’

00:41:23.710 --> 00:41:25.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
So Jehovah says: ‘What?

00:41:25.712 --> 00:41:27.922 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You’re not going to ask for a sign?

00:41:27.922 --> 00:41:30.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, I’m going to give you a sign.’

00:41:30.425 --> 00:41:32.469 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that’s in verse 14:

00:41:33.595 --> 00:41:37.682 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Therefore, Jehovah himself
will give you a sign:

00:41:37.682 --> 00:41:41.478 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Look! The young woman
will become pregnant

00:41:41.478 --> 00:41:45.732 line:90% position:50% align:center
“and will give birth to a son,

00:41:45.732 --> 00:41:48.777 line:90% position:50% align:center
and she will name him Immanuel.”

00:41:50.111 --> 00:41:52.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah assures Ahaz

00:41:52.864 --> 00:41:56.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
that He will protect the line of David,

00:41:56.576 --> 00:41:59.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just with words, notice, but with a sign.

00:41:59.746 --> 00:42:01.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘You’re going to have this son.

00:42:01.748 --> 00:42:04.876 line:90% position:50% align:center
You’re going to see a boy named Immanuel.’

00:42:04.876 --> 00:42:07.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
And that name is not just random.

00:42:07.545 --> 00:42:09.255 line:90% position:50% align:center
The name means something.

00:42:09.255 --> 00:42:11.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
The name means “With Us Is God.”

00:42:11.925 --> 00:42:13.927 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Ahaz, with us is God.

00:42:13.927 --> 00:42:18.431 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I’m not going to allow the covenant
that I made with David to be broken.

00:42:18.431 --> 00:42:21.309 line:90% position:50% align:center
Ahaz, I don’t tell lies,’ Jehovah says.

00:42:21.309 --> 00:42:25.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘I don’t tell lies to David’ (Psalm 89:35)

00:42:26.773 --> 00:42:28.441 line:90% position:50% align:center
—a sign.

00:42:28.441 --> 00:42:30.110 line:90% position:50% align:center
What happens?

00:42:30.110 --> 00:42:34.447 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 16, Jehovah gets more specific:

00:42:35.698 --> 00:42:39.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Before the boy knows how to reject
the bad and choose the good,

00:42:39.661 --> 00:42:42.497 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the land of the two kings whom you dread

00:42:42.497 --> 00:42:45.291 line:90% position:50% align:center
will be completely abandoned.”

00:42:45.291 --> 00:42:48.002 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, notice, that’s exactly what happened.

00:42:48.002 --> 00:42:50.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
The birth of Immanuel held true,

00:42:50.380 --> 00:42:53.842 line:90% position:50% align:center
and before the boy was old enough
to know between good and bad,

00:42:53.842 --> 00:42:57.053 line:90% position:50% align:center
those two kings, Pekah and Rezin,
were killed.

00:42:57.053 --> 00:42:59.055 line:90% position:50% align:center
They were out of the picture.

00:42:59.055 --> 00:43:00.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:43:00.140 --> 00:43:03.726 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because God is with his people.

00:43:03.726 --> 00:43:06.229 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s the lesson: Immanuel.

00:43:07.814 --> 00:43:12.819 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah goes further, chapter 8 and verse 10.

00:43:12.819 --> 00:43:15.989 line:90% position:50% align:center
And what a warning this is for all of us
and for all of those 

00:43:15.989 --> 00:43:19.033 line:90% position:50% align:center
who want to try to oppose
Jehovah’s way of doing things!

00:43:19.033 --> 00:43:21.327 line:90% position:50% align:center
Notice chapter 8 and verse 10.

00:43:21.327 --> 00:43:23.872 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s no conspiracy that can win

00:43:23.872 --> 00:43:27.459 line:90% position:50% align:center
or somehow interrupt Jehovah’s purpose.

00:43:28.501 --> 00:43:30.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
Verse 10 says:

00:43:30.670 --> 00:43:35.550 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Devise a plan, but it will be thwarted!

00:43:35.550 --> 00:43:39.471 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Say what you like, but it will not succeed,

00:43:39.471 --> 00:43:43.016 line:90% position:50% align:center
for God is with us!”

00:43:43.016 --> 00:43:46.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
—a warning to all those who oppose Jehovah.

00:43:46.519 --> 00:43:50.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the days of Hezekiah,
you had the Assyrians—185,000 Assyrians.

00:43:50.857 --> 00:43:53.276 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘Fine!
Camp out near Jerusalem;

00:43:53.276 --> 00:43:55.570 line:90% position:50% align:center
you’re going to die.’—185,000 died.

00:43:55.570 --> 00:43:56.279 line:90% position:50% align:center
Why?

00:43:56.279 --> 00:44:00.658 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because clearly God is with his people
and the royal line of David.

00:44:00.658 --> 00:44:02.785 line:90% position:50% align:center
No conspiracy will succeed.

00:44:04.621 --> 00:44:07.081 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what does this mean for you and me?

00:44:07.081 --> 00:44:09.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
What does this mean for us?

00:44:09.167 --> 00:44:10.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
Does it have meaning?

00:44:10.835 --> 00:44:14.172 line:90% position:50% align:center
Can we have confidence
that God is with us today?

00:44:14.172 --> 00:44:19.177 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now let’s open our Bibles
to Matthew 1:23,

00:44:20.094 --> 00:44:22.096 line:90% position:50% align:center
Matthew 1:23.

00:44:22.096 --> 00:44:25.433 line:90% position:50% align:center
Here we have now the angel
speaking to Joseph about the birth of Jesus.

00:44:25.433 --> 00:44:28.311 line:90% position:50% align:center
But notice what he says in verse 23:

00:44:29.270 --> 00:44:34.067 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘Look! The virgin will become pregnant
and will give birth to a son,

00:44:34.067 --> 00:44:37.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
“‘and they will name him Immanuel’
[there it is again],

00:44:37.487 --> 00:44:42.283 line:90% position:50% align:center
which means, when translated,
‘With Us Is God.’”

00:44:42.283 --> 00:44:44.285 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do we see the connection?

00:44:44.285 --> 00:44:46.496 line:90% position:50% align:center
The name Immanuel comes up again,

00:44:46.496 --> 00:44:49.207 line:90% position:50% align:center
and this time it represents Christ Jesus

00:44:49.207 --> 00:44:53.753 line:90% position:50% align:center
—his role, his leadership, his rulership—

00:44:53.753 --> 00:44:55.755 line:90% position:50% align:center
the title given to Jesus.

00:44:55.755 --> 00:44:57.757 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do we see the connection?

00:44:57.757 --> 00:45:01.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
The prophecy about Immanuel
is completely fulfilled in Jesus.

00:45:01.678 --> 00:45:03.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
He rules as our heavenly King.

00:45:03.680 --> 00:45:06.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
And because of the blessing
and the protection of his rulership,

00:45:06.724 --> 00:45:11.187 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have every reason to declare
with confidence today,

00:45:11.187 --> 00:45:13.731 line:90% position:50% align:center
“With us is God.”

00:45:14.899 --> 00:45:17.026 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you see the signs?

00:45:17.026 --> 00:45:21.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you see the evidence that Jehovah
is giving us to prove he is with us?

00:45:21.990 --> 00:45:26.661 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do you see Jesus living up
to that wonderful name, Immanuel?

00:45:28.538 --> 00:45:30.748 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,

00:45:30.748 --> 00:45:35.503 line:90% position:50% align:center
several weeks ago,
we had a report from the Writing Committee.

00:45:35.503 --> 00:45:39.716 line:90% position:50% align:center
And despite the obstacles of the past year
—do you recall that report?—

00:45:39.716 --> 00:45:42.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
the work in the Writing Department,
Art Department,

00:45:42.302 --> 00:45:46.306 line:90% position:50% align:center
MEPS, Text Processing,
and Translation Services didn’t stop.

00:45:46.306 --> 00:45:49.267 line:90% position:50% align:center
It didn’t even slow down.

00:45:49.267 --> 00:45:53.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
Bible translations in 2019, 33 were released;

00:45:53.313 --> 00:45:55.898 line:90% position:50% align:center
in 2020, 33 were released.

00:45:55.898 --> 00:45:58.776 line:90% position:50% align:center
Add the comments from Wednesday
about a country

00:45:58.776 --> 00:46:00.862 line:90% position:50% align:center
that is now having
more and more Bible studies

00:46:00.862 --> 00:46:04.741 line:90% position:50% align:center
and an increase in interested ones
and baptisms

00:46:04.741 --> 00:46:07.076 line:90% position:50% align:center
—these are more than just updates.

00:46:07.076 --> 00:46:10.747 line:90% position:50% align:center
These are more than just statistics.

00:46:10.747 --> 00:46:13.082 line:90% position:50% align:center
Do we see them as evidences

00:46:13.082 --> 00:46:15.293 line:90% position:50% align:center
that “with us is God”

00:46:15.293 --> 00:46:18.504 line:90% position:50% align:center
and that he is backing us up
in our undertakings?

00:46:18.504 --> 00:46:20.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
That’s what we want to understand.

00:46:20.965 --> 00:46:23.301 line:90% position:50% align:center
No, we’re not perfect.

00:46:23.301 --> 00:46:26.054 line:90% position:50% align:center
We’ll get there at the end
of the Thousand Year Reign.

00:46:26.054 --> 00:46:28.348 line:90% position:50% align:center
But compare the leadership and rulership

00:46:28.348 --> 00:46:32.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
of Immanuel, Christ Jesus,
with the world’s leadership.

00:46:32.101 --> 00:46:34.103 line:90% position:50% align:center
Look what we have.

00:46:34.103 --> 00:46:36.606 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s wonderful to contemplate.

00:46:36.606 --> 00:46:39.275 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what’s the lesson for you and me?

00:46:40.276 --> 00:46:44.656 line:90% position:50% align:center
Don’t miss the clear evidence
that God is with us.

00:46:44.656 --> 00:46:48.493 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep your spiritual vision sharp and clear.

00:46:48.493 --> 00:46:49.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
So here’s a tip.

00:46:51.454 --> 00:46:54.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
After reading a portion of the Bible,

00:46:54.374 --> 00:46:58.211 line:90% position:50% align:center
ask yourself: ‘How did Jehovah

00:46:58.211 --> 00:47:02.382 line:90% position:50% align:center
‘keep his word in this situation?

00:47:02.382 --> 00:47:06.552 line:90% position:50% align:center
How does this show God is with us today?’

00:47:07.720 --> 00:47:10.723 line:90% position:50% align:center
Then take that knowledge and assimilate it

00:47:10.723 --> 00:47:13.351 line:90% position:50% align:center
into your own life
and personal circumstances.

00:47:13.351 --> 00:47:17.563 line:90% position:50% align:center
Build your confidence
in the situation that you are in.

00:47:19.315 --> 00:47:21.859 line:90% position:50% align:center
So, what have we learned?

00:47:21.859 --> 00:47:24.987 line:90% position:50% align:center
(1) When we know that God is with us,

00:47:24.987 --> 00:47:27.990 line:90% position:50% align:center
we are convinced
that he will bless us every time

00:47:27.990 --> 00:47:32.328 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have to bring ourselves
into submission to Jehovah.

00:47:32.328 --> 00:47:36.582 line:90% position:50% align:center
And (2) in Ahaz’s day,

00:47:36.582 --> 00:47:39.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah assured him
that He would protect the line of David,

00:47:39.669 --> 00:47:42.797 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just with words, but with a sign:

00:47:42.797 --> 00:47:46.426 line:90% position:50% align:center
a boy, Immanuel, “With Us Is God.”

00:47:46.426 --> 00:47:51.180 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, Jesus, in his role as Immanuel,
rules as our heavenly King.

00:47:51.180 --> 00:47:53.558 line:90% position:50% align:center
And because of the blessing of his rulership,

00:47:53.558 --> 00:47:58.104 line:90% position:50% align:center
we have every reason to declare
with confidence: “With us is God.”

00:47:58.855 --> 00:48:02.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
The sign of Immanuel is all around us.

00:48:02.066 --> 00:48:06.738 line:90% position:50% align:center
The question is,
Do we see and appreciate the evidence?

00:48:08.197 --> 00:48:11.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah has never abandoned his servants,

00:48:11.159 --> 00:48:13.578 line:90% position:50% align:center
and he will not start with you.

00:48:13.578 --> 00:48:16.914 line:90% position:50% align:center
Keep looking for the evidence
that he is with you now.

